        <LEXMeaning Id="001610001002000" IsBiblicalTerm="Y" EntryCode="27.31" Indent="0">
          <LEXDomains>
            <LEXDomain>Learn</LEXDomain>
          </LEXDomains>
          <LEXSubDomains>
            <LEXSubDomain>Learn Something Against Someone</LEXSubDomain>
          </LEXSubDomains>
          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-10-28 12:01:51" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to obtain information to be used against a person by trying to cause someone to make a mistake</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to try to trap</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to attempt to catch in a mistake</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>It is also possible to understand {L:πειράζω&lt;SDBG:πειράζω:000000&gt;} and {L:ἐκπειράζω&lt;SDBG:ἐκπειράζω:000000&gt;} in {S:04001600100014} and {S:04201002500012} as ‘the process of testing or examining’ (see {D:27.46}). See also {D:88.308}.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
          </LEXSenses>
